The ASKME License

This software is not per se licensed.

Insofar as possible I will document the beneficial behaviours of this software.  
The mere documentation of beneficial properties cannot cause a legal obligation for you to not implement them.  
If you implemented these properties the solution would be isomorphic to my implementation (except, hopefully, the bugs).

If a beneficial behaviour of this software is not documented, then clearly I did not consider it of sufficient value to promote or protect.  
If a harmful behaviour of this software is found I certainly don't want credit for those.

Software is intrinsically a collective and communal effort.  
To that end, if you wish to promote the creation of publicly accessible software the best way to do that is through active participation and engagement in its creation wherever you find the opportunity.

If your legal department requires a formal license to rubber stamp your usage — feel free to ask me.  Or just re-implement it.
